51.2	Cholecystectomy	Cholecystectomy	Cholecystectomy (plural: cholecystectomies) is the surgical removal of the gallbladder. It is the most common method for treating symptomatic gallstones. Surgical options include the standard procedure, called laparoscopic cholecystectomy, and an older more invasive procedure, called open cholecystectomy.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/71/Gallbladderop.jpg/300px-Gallbladderop.jpg
